<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,673,260,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Type locality and stratigraphical range.</emphasis>
Erawan Hill, Chong Sarika sub-district, Phatthana Nikhom district, located about 
<quantity box="[311,383,296,323]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="km" value="13.0">13 km</quantity>
east of 
<collectingRegion box="[474,674,296,322]" country="Thailand" name="Lop Buri" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Lopburi Province</collectingRegion>
, Central 
<collectingCountry box="[777,877,296,322]" name="Thailand" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[893,960,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="1.[151,168,1975,2001]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,1164,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[236,1350,1160,1948]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Geological map of the study location at Erawan Hill, Chong Sarika sub-district, Phatthana Nikhom district, located about 13 km east of Lopburi Province, Central Thailand." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3763909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3763909/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), Khao Khad Formation, 
<collectingRegion box="[1255,1350,296,322]" country="Thailand" name="Sara Buri" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Saraburi</collectingRegion>
Group, Middle Permian, Roadian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,368,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description.</emphasis>
Bellerophontiform, subglobular and slightly compressed shell, higher than wide; anomphalous, umbilical region covered by distinct callus; dorsum evenly rounded; whorls with a distinct slit; slit narrow and rather shallow; whorls covered by numerous closely arranged strengthened growth lines forming almost ribs, growth lines slightly curved backwards towards selenizone at an angle of about 70 degrees; inductura thin, ornamented with several growth lines developed continuing from whorl face; selenizone at periphery, narrow (
<emphasis box="[1156,1168,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">c</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[1182,1268,513,539]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
wide), marked by short curved transverse lunulae, at almost the same distance as of growth lines; aperture reniform in transverse section, tiny V-shaped indentation at crest; lateral lip arched, somewhat angulated after wing-like turnout of lateral lips and smoothly joining anterior lips; outer lip sickle-shaped as suggested by course of growth lines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,657,683]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Montfort" authorityYear="1808" box="[321,458,656,682]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,458,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bellerophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has previously been reported from the Middle Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[1110,1210,656,682]" name="Thailand" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ketwetsuriya" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ketwetsuriya" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="481 - 513" refId="ref24896" refString="Ketwetsuriya, C., Nu ¨ tzel, A. &amp; Kanjanapayont, P. (2016) Permian gastropods from the Tak Fa Limestone, Nakhon Sawan, Northern Thailand. Bulletin of Geosciences, 91, 481 - 513. https: // doi. org / 10.3140 / bull. geosci. 1617" type="journal article" year="2016">
Ketwetsuriya 
<emphasis box="[1381,1429,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ketwetsuriya" box="[222,280,693,719]" firstAuthor="Ketwetsuriya" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="53 - 77" refId="ref24953" refString="Ketwetsuriya, C., Cook, A. G. &amp; Nu ¨ tzel, A. (2020) Permian gastropods from the Ratburi Limestone, Khao Phrik, Central Thai- land. Pala ¨ ontologische Zeitschrift, 94, 53 - 77. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12542 - 019 - 00463 - 0" type="journal article" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
) but it has been treated in open nomenclature because the preservation of that material is too poor for identification. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ketwetsuriya &amp; Karapunar &amp; Charoentitirat &amp; Nützel, 2020" authorityName="Ketwetsuriya &amp; Karapunar &amp; Charoentitirat &amp; Nützel" authorityYear="2020" box="[314,598,728,754]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="erawanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[314,598,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bellerophon erawanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[605,691,729,755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="de Koninck, 1863" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1863" box="[902,1259,728,755]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jonesianus">
<emphasis box="[902,919,729,754]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[933,1053,729,754]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">jonesianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Koninck, L. G. de" box="[1060,1259,728,754]" firstAuthor="de Koninck" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref25516" refString="Koninck, L. G. de (1863) Meimoire sur les Fossiles Paleiozoiques Recueillis dans l'Inde par M. le Docteur Fleming. H. Dessaain, LieIge, 44 pp." type="book" year="1863">de Koninck, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[225,320,764,790]" name="Pakistan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(Chideru), which was also reported from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[975,1070,764,790]" name="Pakistan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(Salt Range) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Waagen" box="[1264,1436,765,791]" firstAuthor="Waagen" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 183" refId="ref28294" refString="Waagen, W. (1880) Salt-Range Fossils. I. Productus Limestone fossils. 2. Pisces-Cephalopoda: supplement Gasteropoda. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India (Palaeontologia Indica), 13, 1 - 183." type="journal article" year="1880">Waagen (1880)</bibRefCitation>
and from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[439,503,801,827]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Akasaka Limestone) by Nützel &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nakazawa" box="[910,1113,800,827]" firstAuthor="Nakazawa" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="103 - 169" refId="ref27024" refString="Nu ¨ tzel, A. &amp; Nakazawa, K. (2012) Permian (Capitanian) gastropods from the Akasaka Limestone (Gifu Prefecture, Japan). Journal of Systematic Palaeontology, 10, 103 - 169. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 14772019.2010.549659" type="journal article" year="2012">Nakazawa (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1863" box="[1125,1391,800,826]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jonesianus">
<emphasis box="[1125,1391,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bellerophon jonesianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a similar ornamentation of pronounced growth lines, a narrow slit and a slightly elevated selenizone. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ketwetsuriya &amp; Karapunar &amp; Charoentitirat &amp; Nützel, 2020" authorityName="Ketwetsuriya &amp; Karapunar &amp; Charoentitirat &amp; Nützel" authorityYear="2020" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="erawanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,837,862]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,291,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">erawanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[297,383,873,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1863" box="[528,678,873,899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jonesianus">
<emphasis box="[528,545,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[558,678,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">jonesianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a less inflated shell, a narrower selenizone, a considerably higher number of fine threads formed by strengthened growth lines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authority="? d'Orbigny, 1840" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1840" box="[199,701,944,971]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sowerbyi" subGenus="Bellerophon">
<emphasis box="[199,216,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[240,377,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bellerophon</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[395,496,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">sowerbyi</emphasis>
? 
<bibRefCitation author="d'Orbigny" box="[516,701,944,971]" firstAuthor="d'Orbigny" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="180 - 218" refId="ref23957" refString="d'Orbigny, A. (1840) Chapter on Bellerophon. In: Ferussac, A. de &amp; d'Orbigny, A. (Eds.), Histoire naturelle generale et particuliere des cephalopods acetabuliferes vivants et fossils. Vol. 1. Antiquariaat Junk, Amsterdam, pp. 180 - 218." type="book chapter" year="1840">d’Orbigny, 1840</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rollins" box="[895,1059,944,971]" firstAuthor="Rollins" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref27384" refString="Rollins, H. B. (1975) Gastropods from the Lower Mississippian Wassonville Limestone in Southeastern Iowa. American Museum Novitates, 2579, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1975">Rollins (1975)</bibRefCitation>
from the Lower Mississippian of Southeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[304,360,981,1007]" country="United States of America" name="Iowa" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Iowa</collectingRegion>
is similar but this species has stronger growth lines and a slightly narrower selenizone. 
<emphasis box="[1361,1378,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1403,1420,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[151,258,1016,1042]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">kingorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yochelson, E. L." box="[263,449,1016,1042]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="205 - 294" refId="ref28745" refString="Yochelson, E. L. (1960) Permian Gastropoda of the southwestern United States. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 119, 205 - 294." type="journal article" year="1960">Yochelson, 1960</bibRefCitation>
from the Permian of the Southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[881,935,1017,1043]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">USA</collectingCountry>
is also similar but has a more globular shape, thicker inductura and deeper slit. 
<emphasis box="[527,544,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[567,584,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[608,731,1052,1078]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">huecoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yochelson, E. L." box="[738,925,1052,1078]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="205 - 294" refId="ref28745" refString="Yochelson, E. L. (1960) Permian Gastropoda of the southwestern United States. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 119, 205 - 294." type="journal article" year="1960">Yochelson, 1960</bibRefCitation>
can be differentiated by a deeper slit, a much more elevated selenizone, reflexed lateral lips and a very large size.
</paragraph>
